Banco BTG Pactual SA, the Brazilian
bank owned by billionaire  Andre Esteves , may sell its 11 percent
stake in  Vanguarda Agro SA (VAGR3)  to three of the agribusinessâ€™s
shareholders, Brasil Economico reported, without saying where it
obtained the information.  BTG Pactual may sell all 247.2 million of its shares to
Enrique Banuelos, Silvio Tini and Helio Seibel, the Sao Paulo-
based newspaper said today. The company originally planned to
auction the shares to investors tomorrow, Brasil Economico said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
